{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The wait time between retries doubles with each consecutive failure, up to a configured maximum.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"MOCK-MISS: This failure is reproducible by directly testing deterministic backoff math (attempt index + cap). REAL-INFRA: No OS/network/subprocess needed. MOCK-HIDE: Mocks do not materially hide arithmetic/capping bugs at this boundary. LLM-DEP/MULTI-STEP: Not applicable.","test_description":"Test a pure backoff calculator (or retry-policy object) with consecutive failure counts: e.g., attempts 1..N produce base*2^k and never exceed maxBackoff. Include boundary cases at and above the cap.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.72,"Integration":0.24,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The retry logic correctly identifies a rate-limit response and computes the appropriate wait time before the next attempt.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: A pure unit test of classifier/backoff helpers can miss wiring bugs between HTTP response mapping and retry policy. REAL-INFRA: No real network required; local in-process fake transport is enough. MOCK-HIDE: Over-mocking the response path could hide misclassification of actual response objects/status fields. LLM-DEP/MULTI-STEP: Not applicable.","test_description":"Wire client + response parser + retry policy with a stub transport returning a 429 (and optional retry headers). Assert the client classifies it as rate-limit and schedules the expected delay value for next attempt.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.76,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"After the wait, the client actually resends the original request and returns the successful result to the caller transparently.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: Unit-testing retry helper alone can miss that the original request is not faithfully replayed by the client wrapper. REAL-INFRA: Can be verified with fake timers + stub transport; no external API required. MOCK-HIDE: If resend is mocked too high-level, a broken replay path may be hidden.","test_description":"Using fake time, have transport return rate-limit once then success. Assert two transport calls occurred, second call payload/method/headers match original request, and `call()` resolves with the success value without exposing retry internals to caller.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.82,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"After the configured maximum number of retries, the client returns a typed `QuotaExhaustedError` rather than a generic error.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: Unit tests of error class alone miss end-to-end retry exhaustion mapping. REAL-INFRA: No OS/network required; deterministic stub failures suffice. MOCK-HIDE: Mocking the retry loop output directly could hide incorrect error translation.","test_description":"Stub transport to always return rate-limit; run client with maxRetries=N and fake timers advancing delays. Assert final rejection is instance of `QuotaExhaustedError` (with expected fields), not a generic error.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.73,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full retry chain — initial call, backoff retries, quota tracking — terminates correctly and does not loop indefinitely before surfacing the error.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: Infinite-loop/termination bugs usually emerge from interaction of retry counter, backoff scheduling, and quota state across modules. REAL-INFRA: Can be caught with local fake clock and bounded assertions; no real HTTP needed. MOCK-HIDE: Mocking each stage independently may always pass while composed chain loops.","test_description":"Run composed client with persistent rate-limit responses, fake timers, and explicit upper bound on attempts/time. Assert chain stops exactly at configured terminal condition and surfaces expected terminal error without additional scheduled retries.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.09,"Integration":0.79,"System":0.11,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Requests issued concurrently from multiple async callers in the same process all draw from the same shared quota bucket.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: Per-call unit tests can miss shared-state bugs (accidentally per-request buckets) under concurrent access. REAL-INFRA: No external systems needed; concurrent promises in-process are sufficient. MOCK-HIDE: Mocking quota service per test call can incorrectly isolate state and hide failures.","test_description":"Create one client instance and issue multiple `call()` invocations concurrently against a stub transport and shared quota manager. Assert aggregate attempt budget/enforcement is global across callers (not per-caller) and resulting pass/fail pattern matches shared bucket rules.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.04,"Integration":0.83,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"When multiple requests are waiting to be sent, they are dispatched in the order they were originally submitted.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: Queue-order bugs come from interaction of scheduler, waiter queue, and async wake-ups; isolated unit checks can miss reordering in composition. REAL-INFRA: In-process deterministic scheduler/fake timers are enough; no real network needed. MOCK-HIDE: If dispatch is mocked at too high a level, FIFO violations will not appear."